      • findDefaultConstructorExternalAnnotations

                                                                               java.lang.String annotationFQN)
        Description copied from class: ExternalAnnotationsManager
        Returns external annotations with fully qualified name of annotationFQN associated with default constructor of the aClass, if the constructor exists. Multiple annotations may be returned since there may be repeatable annotations or annotations from several external annotations roots.
        Specified by:
        findDefaultConstructorExternalAnnotations in class ExternalAnnotationsManager
        Parameters:
        aClass - class of which default constructor's external annotations are to be found
        annotationFQN - fully qualified name of annotation class to search for
        Returns:
        annotations of the default constructor of aClass, or null if the class doesn't have a default constructor.
        See Also:
        ExternalAnnotationsManager.findDefaultConstructorExternalAnnotations(PsiClass)

      • findDefaultConstructorExternalAnnotations

        public java.util.List<PsiAnnotation> findDefaultConstructorExternalAnnotations(PsiClass aClass)
        Description copied from class: ExternalAnnotationsManager
        Returns external annotations associated with default constructor of the aClass, if the constructor exists.

        Default constructors should be handled specially because they don't have PsiModifierListOwner, nor they are returned in PsiClass.getConstructors().

        Yet default constructors may be externally annotated in corresponding annotations.xml: 

         <item name='com.example.Foo Foo()'>
  <annotation name='org.some.Annotation'/>
 </item>
        Specified by:
        findDefaultConstructorExternalAnnotations in class ExternalAnnotationsManager
        Parameters:
        aClass - class of which default constructor's external annotations are to be found
        Returns:
        external annotations of the default constructor of aClass or null if the class doesn't have a default constructor
